rvice couldn't reach cartservice at all\n\nThe trace_analysis_tool shows checkoutservice experiencing high latency when calling cartservice, but the raw trace search doesn't return actual checkoutservice client spans during the anomaly period. This pattern suggests that checkoutservice was attempting to call cartservice but either:\n- The requests never reached cartservice (network issue)\n- Cartservice was unavailable (pod crash)\n- The connection was refused immediately\n\nGiven that the trace_analysis_tool shows both client-side (checkoutservice) and server-side (cartservice) operations with high latency, but my raw trace searches aren't returning checkoutservice-specific spans during the anomaly window, this points to a potential service availability issue rather than just performance degradation.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"rrt_max\", \"checkoutservice->cartservice\", \"hipstershop.CartService/EmptyCart\", \"hipstershop.CartService/GetCart\"],\n  \"affected_components\": [\"checkoutservice\", \"cartservice\"],\n  \"missing_traces\": [\"checkoutservice client spans during anomaly period 2025-06-27T00:10:17Z to 2025-06-27T00:24:17Z\"],\n  \"trace_summary\": \"Trace analysis shows significant latency increase (12-25x) for checkoutservice calls to cartservice during the anomaly period. However, raw trace searches return only frontend→cartservice spans from different time periods, suggesting missing checkoutservice client span data during the actual anomaly window. This indicates checkoutservice may have been unable to properly connect to cartservice or experienced immediate connection failures.\",\n  \"next_verification\": {\n    \"action\": \"check_pod_status_at_timestamp\",\n    \"reason\": \"Missing checkoutservice client spans during anomaly period suggests potential pod crashes or network connectivity issues\",\n    \"suggested_metrics\": [\"pod_processes\", \"network_connectivity\", \"connection_refused_count\"],\n    \"suggested_log_keywords